It's okay to acknowledge problems with shit that seemed super cool when you were 14 that doesn't really hold up when you've got a better understanding of the medium. He wrote a solid trilogy that could have been extended to 5-6 volumes and instead bloated it to 15 because the money was nice. I'd probably have done the same in his shoes. Doesn't change the fact that half the books are dogshit.
You paint such a picture that I can't wait to try and read the whole series!
:wink:

I honestly can't recommend a series where half the books are filler. I think the first four are generally excellent, and I have plenty of good to say about the series overall, but I can't in good conscious tell someone to read a series where there's so much obvious treading of water.

There's one, 6-7 I think, where the first 1/5 or so of it is a re-hash of the massive battle that ended the previous book, told from a different POV, that really doesn't relay any new information. He just burns 150 pages or something showing it from a different camera angle.
The Sword of Truth novels by Goodkind had some serious filler.
And the final book was a travesty that he must have shat out in a month.
